collections.description: Team: The Asociación Atlética Argentinos Juniors was founded on August 15, 1904 in the neighborhood of La Paternal, City of Buenos Aires. Is one of the 11 classic teams in Argentina. Recognized for training players like: Diego Armando Maradona, Fernando Redondo, Andrés D'Alessandro, Juan Román Riquelme, Claudio Borghi, Esteban Cambiasso, Sergio Batista, Juan Pablo Sorin, Fernando Cáceres, Leonel Gancedo, Diego Placente, Nicolás Pareja, Néstor Ortigoza, Lucas Biglia, Lucas Barrios, Federico Insúa, Leonardo Pisculichi. Argentinos Juniors won 3 local championships (1984, 1985, 2010), a 1985 Libertadores Cup and the 1986 Inter-American Cup. One of the best teams to live the experience with the local fans. Buy your tickets and enjoy also the prematch and postmatch at Diego Maradona Stadium! Stadium: The Diego Maradona Stadium is special, not only for its name, also because Argentinos Juniors was the team were Maradona debuts back in 1976. The stadium has a capacity for 24.000 spectators and is located in La Paternal neighborhood. Don't miss the opportunity to live the pre and post match with a local fan. Buy the full experience, select your match, select your host and buy Argentinos Juniors tickets.
collections.title: Argentinos Juniors Tickets & Experiences
collections.descriptionHtml:
Team:

The Asociación Atlética Argentinos Juniors was founded on August 15, 1904 in the neighborhood of La Paternal, City of Buenos Aires. Is one of the 11 classic teams in Argentina.

Recognized for training players like: Diego Armando Maradona, Fernando Redondo, Andrés D'Alessandro, Juan Román Riquelme, Claudio Borghi, Esteban Cambiasso, Sergio Batista, Juan Pablo Sorin, Fernando Cáceres, Leonel Gancedo, Diego Placente, Nicolás Pareja, Néstor Ortigoza, Lucas Biglia, Lucas Barrios, Federico Insúa, Leonardo Pisculichi.

Argentinos Juniors won 3 local championships (1984, 1985, 2010), a 1985 Libertadores Cup and the 1986 Inter-American Cup.

One of the best teams to live the experience with the local fans. Buy your tickets and enjoy also the prematch and postmatch at Diego Maradona Stadium!

Stadium:

The Diego Maradona Stadium is special, not only for its name, also because Argentinos Juniors was the team were Maradona debuts back in 1976.

The stadium has a capacity for 24.000 spectators and is located in La Paternal neighborhood. Don't miss the opportunity to live the pre and post match with a local fan. Buy the full experience, select your match, select your host and buy Argentinos Juniors tickets.
